<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../manrev.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>spzeros</TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function</TYPE>
  <DATE>January 1995</DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="spzeros">  sparse zero matrix</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>sp=spzeros(nrows,ncols)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>sp=spzeros(A)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
    <PARAM_INDENT>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>nrows</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: integer (number of rows)</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>ncols</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: integer (number os columns)</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>A</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: sparse matrix</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>sp</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: sparse zero matrix</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
    </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
    <P><VERB>sp=spzeros(nrows,ncols)</VERB> returns a sparse zero matrix <VERB>sp</VERB> 
    with <VERB>nrows</VERB> rows, <VERB>ncols</VERB> columns. 
    (Equivalent to <VERB>sparse([],[],[nrow,ncols])</VERB>)</P>
    <P><VERB>sp=spzeros(A)</VERB> returns a sparse zero matrix with same
    dimensions as <VERB>A</VERB>. If <VERB>[m,n]=size(A)</VERB>, <VERB>spzeros(m,n)</VERB> and
    <VERB>spzeros(A)</VERB> are equivalent. In particular <VERB>spzeros(3)</VERB> is not
    equivalent to <VERB>spzeros(3,3)</VERB>.</P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE>
<![CDATA[
sum(spzeros(1000,1000))
 ]]>
  </EXAMPLE>
